    <h1>The data</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201101/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-01"><time>2020-11-01</time></a>
        - <span>WORLD</span>
        - <span role="byline">REUTERS, BLOOMBERG</span>
    </section>

    <p>• Ant Group is a fi­nan­cial ser­vices com­po­nent of bil­lion­aire founder Jack Ma’s Alibaba em­pire. • Based in Hangzhou, fast-grow­ing Ant op­er­ates China’s big­gest pay­ments plat­form and other fi­nan­cial ser­vices.</p>
    <p>• It started as a pay­ments pro­ces­sor in 2004, later of­fer­ing users short-term loans that are cred­ited within min­utes, and sell­ing in­sur­ance and in­vest­ment prod­ucts.</p>
    <p>• Ant’s list­ing in Hong Kong is ex­pected to raise US$34.4 bil­lion (S$47 bil­lion), the world’s big­gest IPO that will sur­pass the US$29.4 bil­lion raised last De­cem­ber by Saudi Aramco.</p>
    <p>• Bids by re­tail in­vestors to buy Ant shares to­talled US$3 tril­lion, equiv­a­lent to the gross do­mes­tic prod­uct of the United King­dom. • In­vestors, both re­tail and in­sti­tu­tional, are bank­ing on hopes that Ant will con­tinue to ben­e­fit from the rapid digi­ti­sa­tion of fi­nan­cial ser­vices in China. • Mr Ma, 56, is poised to be­come the world’s 11th rich­est per­son af­ter the Ant IPO. His 8.8 per cent Ant stake is worth US$27.4 bil­lion based on the stock pric­ing, tak­ing his to­tal for­tune to US$71.6 bil­lion.</p>


